cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Seamless, please cite it as below."
title: "Seamless"
abstract: >-
  Seamless is a workflow tool for scientific computing that wraps existing
  Python and command-line code as reproducible, cached transformations.
  Define your computation once — cache it, scale it, share it.
type: software
license: MIT
authors:
